comments.value:
Hi Janos,

Can you take a look at this (in terms of priority it's kind of just below mailing lists and mobile, but the nearer we get to the launch of the French site, hopefully no more than 2/3 weeks away the more urgent this will become)

The font on the French site had got increased due to the /fr prefix
http://new2012.kitsite.com/kit/preview/fr/games/olympic-sports/football.php
http://new2012.kitsite.com/kit/preview/games/olympic-sports/football.php

The Months on the News templates/section will also need to be amended (we don't have a French news section yet)
http://new2012.kitsite.com/kit/preview/news/index.php

Ideally we'd use labels (see below) but am I right in thinking your writing the Navigation out in PHP?

If so:
1) how hard would it be to re-code in Rhino (assume this isn't an option but thought I'd ask)
2) can we code the PHP to render French months in the News navigation (via a hash/lookup table in PHP - the translation for Months are in the Label bundle or on the old site)

The old site is here (although we are no longer having French urls, it's now just the English path with a /fr prefix)
http://old.london2012.com/fr/actus/archives/index.php (stratford/design)

Please can you keep track of time spent on this and *let me know* (rather than adding it to this ticket) as we want to work out how much time in total we have spent on the French site.

thanks

Jamie


getLabel: function(name, locale, en)
   // A wrapper around kit.getLabel()
   // This wrapper is so that we can display a warning message when
   // in "preview" mode.
   // In "publish" mode, if there's no value found for the specified
   // locale, we just output the english value. Which is wrong but
   // better than nothing and better than an error message.
   // You should only ever need to call:
   //   Lang.getLabel("Label name");
   // "locale" will get derived from the current page.
   // "en" never needs to be set (afaics).

